  "prompt": "What do if I forget my user id and password of forex card HDFC?",
  "response": "If you've forgotten your user ID and password for your HDFC Forex Card, you can follow these steps to recover them:\n\n### For User ID Recovery:\n1. **Visit HDFC Bank's Official Website:** Go to the official HDFC Bank website.\n2. **Navigate to Forex Card Section:** Find the section dedicated to Forex Cards.\n3. **User ID Recovery Option:** Look for the option related to User ID recovery.\n4. **Enter Required Details:** You may need to provide details such as your registered email ID, mobile number, or Forex Card number.\n5. **Follow Instructions:** Follow the on-screen instructions to retrieve your User ID.\n\n### For Password Recovery:\n1. **Go to Login Page:** Visit the login page of the HDFC Forex Card online portal.\n2. **Click on \u201cForgot Password\u201d:** Look for the option that says \"Forgot Password\" or similar.\n3. **Enter Necessary Information:** Provide the details that are required, such as your User ID and other verification information.\n4. **Receive Reset Link:** You\u2019ll typically receive a password reset link via your registered email or SMS on your registered mobile number.\n5. **Create a New Password:** Follow the link and instructions to create a new password.\n\n### Additional Help:\n- **Customer Support:** If you're unable to reset your User ID or password using the above methods, consider contacting HDFC Bank customer support. You can reach them through the helpline number provided on their website or visit a branch for assistance.\n- **Mobile Banking App:** If you have the HDFC Bank mobile banking app, you might also find options to recover your login credentials directly through the app.\n\nAlways ensure you're using secure methods and official channels to recover your details to protect your personal information.",
